<Link id="l00762" /><CodeLine lineNumber="762"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Below is the pattern that is used to figure out the archive format</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00763" /><CodeLine lineNumber="763"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// GNU archive format</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00764" /><CodeLine lineNumber="764"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  First member : / (may exist, if it exists, points to the symbol table )</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00765" /><CodeLine lineNumber="765"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  Second member : // (may exist, if it exists, points to the string table)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00766" /><CodeLine lineNumber="766"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  Note : The string table is used if the filename exceeds 15 characters</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00767" /><CodeLine lineNumber="767"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// BSD archive format</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00768" /><CodeLine lineNumber="768"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  First member : &#95;&#95;.SYMDEF or &quot;&#95;&#95;.SYMDEF SORTED&quot; (the symbol table)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00769" /><CodeLine lineNumber="769"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  There is no string table, if the filename exceeds 15 characters or has a</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00770" /><CodeLine lineNumber="770"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  embedded space, the filename has #1/&lt;size&gt;, The size represents the size</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00771" /><CodeLine lineNumber="771"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  of the filename that needs to be read after the archive header</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00772" /><CodeLine lineNumber="772"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// COFF archive format</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00773" /><CodeLine lineNumber="773"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  First member : /</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00774" /><CodeLine lineNumber="774"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  Second member : / (provides a directory of symbols)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00775" /><CodeLine lineNumber="775"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  Third member : // (may exist, if it exists, contains the string table)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00776" /><CodeLine lineNumber="776"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  Note: Microsoft PE/COFF Spec 8.3 says that the third member is present</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00777" /><CodeLine lineNumber="777"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  even if the string table is empty. However, lib.exe does not in fact</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00778" /><CodeLine lineNumber="778"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  seem to create the third member if there&#39;s no member whose filename</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00779" /><CodeLine lineNumber="779"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  exceeds 15 characters. So the third member is optional.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00780" /><CodeLine lineNumber="780"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
